<TITLE> Garos celebrate Wangala </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 04 (bdnews24.com)  Wangala, the harvest festival of the Garos (Mandi), was held on Friday in the capital, where 10,000 of the tribe live. Wangala, a religious festival of the Garos, is held in honour of Saljong, the Sun-god of fertility. The celebration of the Wangala festival marks the end of a period of toil, which brings good output of the fields. It also signifies the onset of winter. Nearly 200,000 Garos live in Bangladesh, mostly in Mymensingh. The day-long festival was marked by a fair, music and dances. Many people from other parts of the country also joined the festival. Home minister Shahara Khatun, disaster management minister Abdur Razzak were present a function held in celebration of the festival. b
